,Recommended,412270,20053282,"Posted: 28 December, 2015",all,tsunamiDry,"Stories of Bethem is quite a charming game. The gameplay compares well to old Zelda games like Link to the Past. You are without a sword, though, and all your abilities use mana instead making mana management important. The abilities/spells you aquire are interesting, they add new fighting mechanics, and unlock new areas for you to explore in both new and already explored maps. Exploration always feels important and rewarding. Still getting updates!Pros:Fun explorationQuality puzzlesUnique abilitiesGreat level designNice, coherent art-styleGreat post-release supportCons:Mediocre writingSlow natural mana regeneration"
